  <tr>
    <td><p>1. Wh-question ask for information Most questions<br/>
         use a Wh-word + do or does + a subject + the base<br/>
         form of the verb</p></td>
    <td><p>Wh-word   do/does    subject base form<br/>
        Q: When do you go to bed?<br/>
        Q: What does he dream about?</p></td> 
 
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><p>2. To  ask a question about the subject, use who or what<br/>
        + The third-person singular form of the verb</p></td>

    <td><p>- Who sleeps on the futon?sleeps on the futon?<br/>
        subject<br/>
          My brother sleeps on the futon<br/>
        - What helps you fall asleep?<br/>
         subject<br/>   
        - Milk helps me fall asleep.</p>        
      </td> 
    </tr>

  <tr>
    <td><p>BE CAREFUL! Do not use do or does with questions<br/>
        about the subject. Do not use the base formof the verb</p></td>

    <td><p>NOT:Who (does) sleeps on the futon?<br/>
           NOT:Who (do) sleeps on the futon?<br/>
           NOT: Who (sleep) on the futon?<br/>
   
        </p>        
      </td> 
    </tr>
   <tr>
